==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*-hād'' (originally a noun, represented by Old English [[had|hād]]).  Cognate with Old Saxon [[-hed|-hēd]] (Dutch [[-heid]]), Old High German [[-heit]] (German [[-heit]]).

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /ha:d/

===Suffix===
'''-hād'''
# forming nouns of condition or quality, from nouns or adjectives

